The paper deals with the maintenance of maximal bicliques in a dynamic bipartite graph, which is a problem in graph algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, which suggests categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, indicating a possible fit with cs.AL (Algorithms).
